00:31:46.400 --> 00:31:50.400
..Amélie is the only one
to know the key to the enigma..

254
00:31:50.400 --> 00:31:53.400
..of the mystery-man
of the photo machines.

255
00:31:55.400 --> 00:31:58.400
-'Morning. Mrs Walace.
How are you ?

256
00:31:59.400 --> 00:32:02.200
-Always better
when it's not raining.

257
00:32:02.400 --> 00:32:05.400
-Here. for you.
-For me ?

258
00:32:13.400 --> 00:32:14.400
"Mrs Walace.

259
00:32:14.400 --> 00:32:17.400
"After the recent discovery
of a mailbag that was lost..

260
00:32:17.400 --> 00:32:20.400
"..when a plane disappeared .
on the 12th of October 1969.

261
00:32:21.400 --> 00:32:25.400
"La Poste has the pleasure
to deliver to you a letter..

262
00:32:25.400 --> 00:32:28.400
"..that was addressed to you.
Please accept..

263
00:32:28.400 --> 00:32:31.400
"..all our apologies
for this unusual delay.

264
00:32:31.400 --> 00:32:35.400
Jacques Grosjean.
Head of the Public Relations department."

265
00:32:35.400 --> 00:32:37.400
"Mado my love.

266
00:32:37.400 --> 00:32:41.400
"I'm in exile. I can't sleep.
I think about you all the time.

267
00:32:41.400 --> 00:32:45.400
"I made the worst mistake
of my life.

268
00:32:45.400 --> 00:32:47.400
"I gave up the money
and that woman.

269
00:32:47.400 --> 00:32:51.400
If everything works out. I will
soon buy a house."

270
00:32:52.400 --> 00:32:55.400
"I catch myself
dreaming of better days..

271
00:32:55.400 --> 00:32:58.400
"..that you'll forgive me
and that you'll come and join me.

272
00:32:59.400 --> 00:33:03.400
Your Adrien
who's always loved you so much."

273
00:33:30.400 --> 00:33:34.400
-Here. M. Dufayel.
you've got mail.

274
00:33:42.400 --> 00:33:43.400
M. Dufayel...

275
00:33:43.400 --> 00:33:46.400
..you know what happened
to the caretaker this morning ?

276
00:33:47.400 --> 00:33:48.400
-A letter.

277
00:33:48.400 --> 00:33:52.400
-From her husband.
40 years late.

278
00:33:54.400 --> 00:33:58.000
Quite a long time.
isn't it. M. Dufayel ?

279
00:34:07.400 --> 00:34:11.400
That's 'cause I don't really like
still lifes. M. Dufayel.

280
00:34:11.400 --> 00:34:15.400
-In the meantime.
take care over your light layer.

281
00:34:15.400 --> 00:34:18.200
It's dark on light. always!

282
00:34:34.400 --> 00:34:37.400
-M. Dufayel ?
-Yes!

283
00:34:37.400 --> 00:34:42.400
-The papers say that there's soon
gonna be a new star.

284
00:34:43.200 --> 00:34:45.400
-You're interested in stars?

285
00:34:45.400 --> 00:34:49.000
-I saw this show at my mum's.
that's why.

286
00:34:49.400 --> 00:34:52.400
but I dunno if it's true.

287
00:34:52.400 --> 00:34:54.400
It's the les Americans...

288
00:34:54.400 --> 00:34:57.800
They're gonna take the ashes
of rich dead people...

289
00:34:58.400 --> 00:35:02.400
..to put them in a satellite.
and send it into space.

290
00:35:02.400 --> 00:35:06.000
And it's gonna shine forever.
the satellite.

291
00:35:08.400 --> 00:35:12.400
And Lady Di ?
You think they're gonna do the same for her?

292
00:35:12.400 --> 00:35:14.400
-Lady Di !!

293
00:35:14.400 --> 00:35:17.800
You're getting on my nerves !!
I can't concentrate!!

294
00:35:19.400 --> 00:35:21.400
Lady Di...

295
00:35:23.400 --> 00:35:25.400
Renoir !

296
00:37:01.400 --> 00:37:03.400
-Morning. sir.

297
00:37:17.400 --> 00:37:20.400
-Cambodia...

298
00:37:22.400 --> 00:37:24.400
I don't get that.

299
00:37:24.400 --> 00:37:27.400
I don't get it!

300
00:37:27.400 --> 00:37:30.920
-That was wonderful!
You couldn't have done better.

301
00:37:31.400 --> 00:37:34.400
-Did it work ?
-It's running it's course.

302
00:37:34.400 --> 00:37:37.400
-Well. I'll do it again any time!
The harm is done anyway...

303
00:37:37.400 --> 00:37:38.400
-Quoi ?

304
00:37:38.400 --> 00:37:40.400
-They call me Snow White.
now!

305
00:38:37.960 --> 00:38:43.400
"bar 'les 2..."
"I am often..."

306
00:38:43.400 --> 00:38:45.400
"bar 'les 2 Moulins'
I am often there

307
00:38:45.400 --> 00:38:46.520
after 4 pm"

308
00:38:51.400 --> 00:38:53.800
-Eva ?
*-Yes ?

309
00:38:54.200 --> 00:38:58.400
-Could you take over at 4pm please ?

310
00:38:58.400 --> 00:39:00.400
*-Oh. you're pushing it!

311
00:39:07.400 --> 00:39:08.400
-What's going on?

312
00:39:09.400 --> 00:39:12.400
Is he sulking?
-He thinks I smile too much.

313
00:39:12.400 --> 00:39:16.400
-He prefers when it when you frown?
-With other men. yes.

314
00:39:18.400 --> 00:39:22.400
-Nino's late. For Amélie.
there's only two possible explanations

315
00:39:23.400 --> 00:39:25.400
1. He didn't find the picture.

316
00:39:25.400 --> 00:39:29.400
2. He didn't have time to piece it together..

317
00:39:29.400 --> 00:39:33.400
..because 3 repeat offenders
took him hostage.

318
00:39:34.400 --> 00:39:36.400
Chased by the police...

319
00:39:36.400 --> 00:39:37.400
..they managed to escape.

320
00:39:37.400 --> 00:39:40.400
But he caused an accident.

321
00:39:40.400 --> 00:39:45.400
When he recovered.
he couldn't remember anything.

322
00:39:46.400 --> 00:39:47.400
A trucker gave him a ride..

323
00:39:48.400 --> 00:39:51.400
..and believing that he is a fugitive.
put him in a container to Istanbul.

324
00:39:52.400 --> 00:39:54.400
There. he came across
Afghan adventurers...

325
00:39:55.400 --> 00:39:58.400
..who took him with them
to steal soviet missiles.

326
00:40:02.400 --> 00:40:05.400
But their lorry exploded
on a landmine in Tajikistan.

327
00:40:05.400 --> 00:40:08.400
The only survivor. mountaineers
helped him out...

328
00:40:08.400 --> 00:40:10.400
..and he became
a mujaheddin fighter.

329
00:40:10.400 --> 00:40:13.400
Thus. Amélie really doesn't see
why she should worry so much..

330
00:40:13.400 --> 00:40:15.400
..for a guy who'll spend the
rest of his life eating bortsch...

331
00:40:15.400 --> 00:40:18.400
..with a stupid hat
on his head !

332
00:40:35.400 --> 00:40:39.400
-Hi. what can I get you?
-A coffee. please.

333
00:40:39.400 --> 00:40:41.400
-One coffee!

334
00:41:01.400 --> 00:41:05.400
Here's your coffee.

335
00:41:05.400 --> 00:41:06.800
-Thanks.

336
00:41:39.400 --> 00:41:41.400
-Now. he's understood.

337
00:41:41.400 --> 00:41:44.400
He's going to put down his spoon...

338
00:41:46.400 --> 00:41:49.400
and pick up the sugar
on the table with his finger.

339
00:41:54.400 --> 00:41:56.400
Then he'll turn around..

340
00:41:57.400 --> 00:42:00.400
..and then. he'll talk to me.

341
00:42:04.400 --> 00:42:05.400
-Excuse me !

342
00:42:06.400 --> 00:42:08.400
Is this you ?

343
00:42:12.400 --> 00:42:15.400
Yes. that's you.

344
00:42:36.400 --> 00:42:40.400
-Let me clear the table for you.

345
00:42:40.400 --> 00:42:41.400
Another coffee?

346
00:42:42.400 --> 00:42:45.400
-No. thanks. I'm fine.

347
00:43:03.400 --> 00:43:08.400
-So that's the one. there.
the guy who raises his hand?

348
00:43:08.400 --> 00:43:10.200
-Yes.

349
00:43:12.400 --> 00:43:15.400
-Is she in love with him?

350
00:43:17.400 --> 00:43:19.400
-Yes.

351
00:43:19.400 --> 00:43:23.400
-The time has come for her
to take some real risks.

352
00:43:24.400 --> 00:43:28.400
-Well yes. she's thinking about it.
She's thinking of a stratagem...

353
00:43:28.400 --> 00:43:32.400
-Yes. she likes stratagems.
doesn't she !

354
00:43:33.400 --> 00:43:34.990
-Yes.

355
00:43:36.400 --> 00:43:38.400
She's a bit of a coward.

356
00:43:38.400 --> 00:43:44.400
That's why I have trouble
with her eyes.

357
00:43:44.920 --> 00:43:47.560
"Raymond Dufayel's meddling..

358
00:43:47.800 --> 00:43:49.880
"..is intolerable!

359
00:43:52.360 --> 00:43:55.360
"If Amélie prefers to..

360
00:43:55.360 --> 00:43:58.030
"live in a dream-world..

361
00:43:58.030 --> 00:44:02.120
"and live her whole life
as an introvert. it's her right.

362
00:44:02.120 --> 00:44:03.600
"Because...

363
00:44:03.600 --> 00:44:06.600
"..making a mess of your life
is an indefeasible right!"

364
00:44:39.400 --> 00:44:42.400
-What are you doing. M. Dufayel ?

365
00:44:42.990 --> 00:44:45.400
-Tell me. Lucien my boy...

366
00:44:45.400 --> 00:44:48.400
..for your deliveries...

367
00:44:48.400 --> 00:44:52.400
..do you still have the keys
of the other tenants ?

368
00:45:03.400 --> 00:45:07.400
-good morning. sir.
One of your machines is out of order.

369
00:45:07.400 --> 00:45:11.400
Er... No. but I think
there's something stuck.

370
00:45:11.400 --> 00:45:14.400
Gare de l'Est.
lounge of the Lost Steps.

371
00:45:17.400 --> 00:45:19.400
-Buy 10. 1 free.
-No. thanks.

372
00:45:26.400 --> 00:45:26.400
-Sam !

373
00:45:28.400 --> 00:45:28.400
Samantha !

374
00:45:31.400 --> 00:45:33.400
Samantha !

375
00:45:38.400 --> 00:45:39.400
-Can you take over from...

376
00:45:54.160 --> 00:45:56.240
"Can you..."

377
00:45:59.200 --> 00:46:01.200
"Can you take over from me this afternoon?"

378
00:46:01.470 --> 00:46:03.080
"Be at the lounge
of the Lost Steps

379
00:46:03.080 --> 00:46:05.400
Gare de l'Est
Tuesday 5pm"

380
00:47:15.400 --> 00:47:18.400
-Just a second. I've finished.

381
00:47:21.400 --> 00:47:25.400
-The mystery man of the
photo machines wasn't a ghost...

382
00:47:25.400 --> 00:47:28.400
..nor somebody obsessed by the fear
of ageing. but the repairman.

383
00:47:28.400 --> 00:47:31.800
Just a technician
doing his job. That's all.

384
00:47:33.400 --> 00:47:35.400
-Excuse me...

385
00:48:17.400 --> 00:48:21.400
-He's watching me like a dog.
It drives me crazy.

386
00:48:22.400 --> 00:48:25.400
-4.05pm. public show
of feminine conspiracy.

387
00:48:26.400 --> 00:48:29.400
-Ow. you look tense. Georgette.
you look tense.

388
00:48:29.400 --> 00:48:31.400
Courage. it's not easy.

389
00:48:38.400 --> 00:48:39.400
-Excuse me.

390
00:48:39.400 --> 00:48:42.400
Is this yours?
-Yes. but it's not me who...

391
00:48:43.400 --> 00:48:44.400
-I know it's not you.
Where can I find her ?

392
00:48:45.400 --> 00:48:46.400
-She's at her father's.

393
00:48:46.400 --> 00:48:51.400
It bothers me. I'd like to
talk to you. I finish at 6.

394
00:48:51.400 --> 00:48:54.400
Can  you drop by ?
-Sure.

395
00:48:54.400 --> 00:48:55.400
-See you later.

396
00:48:55.400 --> 00:48:59.400
-There you are. 4.08pm.
The trap is set.

397
00:49:29.400 --> 00:49:32.400
-And the blond guy. with
the camelhair jacket?

398
00:49:32.400 --> 00:49:36.400
He's absent-minded too ?
-What do you mean ?

399
00:49:36.400 --> 00:49:38.920
-He also came back 3 times.

400
00:49:39.400 --> 00:49:41.400
1.12 pm...

401
00:49:41.400 --> 00:49:43.400
"Camelhair".
2.50 pm...

402
00:49:44.400 --> 00:49:45.400
"Camelhair".

403
00:49:46.400 --> 00:49:48.400
4.17 pm... "Camelhair"...
-Stop it!!!

404
00:49:48.400 --> 00:49:51.400
My red patches are appearing.
again. Look!

405
00:49:52.400 --> 00:49:55.800
Mrs Suzanne. It starts again!!
He's gonna drive me crazy!

406
00:49:56.400 --> 00:49:57.400
-Don't start again!

407
00:49:58.400 --> 00:50:01.400
-If she had a clear conscience
she wouldn't be upset.

408
00:50:02.400 --> 00:50:03.400
-I'm going home!

409
00:50:04.400 --> 00:50:07.400
A psycho !!
That's the limit!

410
00:50:08.400 --> 00:50:09.400
-Georgette !

411
00:50:09.400 --> 00:50:11.400
Are you done. suffocating them
like that?

412
00:50:12.400 --> 00:50:14.400
A woman needs space to breathe.

413
00:50:15.400 --> 00:50:17.400
-Yes. and then.
she goes elsewhere.

414
00:50:18.400 --> 00:50:19.400
-It can be good sometimes!

415
00:50:20.400 --> 00:50:22.400
-Oh you. the writing failure!

416
00:50:23.400 --> 00:50:25.400
-Yes... writing failure.
a failure...

417
00:50:26.400 --> 00:50:28.400
I like this word: "failure".

418
00:50:28.400 --> 00:50:31.400
That's human destiny.
-He's getting pedantic!

419
00:50:31.400 --> 00:50:34.400
Failure after failure.
you make drafts and nothing more.

420
00:50:35.400 --> 00:50:39.400
Life's only an
endless repetition.

421
00:50:40.400 --> 00:50:42.400
-Yeah. right!
He didn't even come up with that himself!

422
00:50:42.400 --> 00:50:46.400
-I do have ideas on my own. you know.

423
00:50:46.400 --> 00:50:49.400
People always steal them from me.
A bit like you with women.

424
00:50:50.400 --> 00:50:52.400
-What does that mean?

425
00:50:52.400 --> 00:50:55.400
-Maybe you should
resign yourself.

426
00:50:55.400 --> 00:50:57.400
-Mind your own business. you...

427
00:50:57.400 --> 00:50:59.400
-Yes. what. eh ?!?
-Stop it!

428
00:51:00.400 --> 00:51:03.400
-What's going on here?

429
00:51:03.400 --> 00:51:06.400
-Georgette wanted to go for a walk
and Joseph makes a fuss.

430
00:51:07.400 --> 00:51:08.400
-A walk. right!

431
00:51:08.400 --> 00:51:13.400
Yes. like Gina
and the guy with the plastic bag...

432
00:51:13.400 --> 00:51:17.400
Hold on. I saw the whole process.

433
00:51:17.400 --> 00:51:20.400
First the little note in the pocket

434
00:51:20.400 --> 00:51:23.400
At 4.08 pm. So the guy comes back
today and there you go !

435
00:51:24.400 --> 00:51:25.400
They go for a walk.

436
00:51:29.400 --> 00:51:32.400
-The problem is.
you look nice to me.

437
00:51:32.400 --> 00:51:33.400
-Which means?

438
00:51:33.400 --> 00:51:37.400
-The more I like a guy.
the less he's structured mentally.

439
00:51:37.400 --> 00:51:41.400
I'd like to know more.
-Ask me questions.

440
00:51:42.400 --> 00:51:45.400
-What doesn't a swallow make?

441
00:51:45.400 --> 00:51:48.400
-A swallow ?
A summer.

442
00:51:49.400 --> 00:51:52.000
-And clothes?
-The man.

443
00:51:52.400 --> 00:51:53.400
-When the cat's away...
-The mice will play.

444
00:51:53.400 --> 00:51:55.400
-Slow and steady...
-Wins the race.

445
00:51:55.400 --> 00:51:57.400
-A rolling stone...
-Gathers no moss.

446
00:51:57.400 --> 00:51:59.400
-He that will steal a penny...
-Will steal a pound.

447
00:51:59.400 --> 00:52:02.400
-Out of sight...
-Out of mind.

448
00:52:02.400 --> 00:52:04.400
-Not bad!
-More ?

449
00:52:05.400 --> 00:52:10.400
-I think that those who know the proverbs
can't be bad persons.

450
00:52:10.400 --> 00:52:14.400
-Oh. the pretty girl
from the 5th floor !

451
00:52:14.400 --> 00:52:18.400
I've got to tell you.
Do you believe in miracles?

452
00:52:18.400 --> 00:52:20.400
-Not today. no.

453
00:52:21.400 --> 00:52:23.400
-You'll be surprised

454
00:52:23.400 --> 00:52:26.400
Some mountaineers..

455
00:52:26.400 --> 00:52:29.400
..on the Mont-Blanc
discovered...

456
00:53:05.400 --> 00:53:08.400
-Hi Lucien.
Do you have yeast?

457
00:53:08.400 --> 00:53:10.400
-Is it for Miss Amélie ?
-Yes.

458
00:53:10.400 --> 00:53:16.400
-She's cooking. right?
Collignon. go fetch.

459
00:54:06.400 --> 00:54:09.400
-Amélie ? Amélie ?

460
00:54:16.400 --> 00:54:19.400
Amélie ?

461
00:55:09.400 --> 00:55:12.400
*-Go to the bedroom.
Miss Poulain.

462
00:55:27.400 --> 00:55:30.400
All right... Amélie. my girl...

463
00:55:31.400 --> 00:55:37.400
You don't have glass bones like me.
you can knock against life

464
00:55:38.400 --> 00:55:41.400
If you let this opportunity
slip away...

465
00:55:42.400 --> 00:55:44.400
..then. as time goes by...

466
00:55:45.400 --> 00:55:48.400
..it's your heart that will become...

467
00:55:48.400 --> 00:55:51.400
..as dry and fragile..

468
00:55:51.400 --> 00:55:54.400
..as my bones

469
00:55:54.400 --> 00:55:57.400
So...

470
00:55:57.400 --> 00:56:00.400
Go for it!
For Christ's sake!

471
00:56:15.400 --> 00:56:17.400
-I...

472
00:58:00.400 --> 00:58:01.400
-Hey !

473
00:59:40.400 --> 00:59:42.400
-To the International Airport

474
00:59:42.400 --> 00:59:46.400
-Today's September 28. 1997.
it's 11 o'clock in the morning

475
00:59:47.400 --> 00:59:49.400
At the Trône Fair

476
00:59:49.400 --> 00:59:52.400
..the marshmallow-mixing machine
mixes marshmallow.

477
00:59:53.400 --> 00:59:56.400
At the same moment. at the La Villette
garden Félix L'Herbier discovers...

478
00:59:56.400 --> 00:59:58.400
..that the number of possible connexions
in a human brain..

479
00:59:58.400 --> 01:00:02.400
..is superior to the number of atomes
in the universe. Meanwhile...

480
01:00:02.400 --> 01:00:05.400
..at the foot of the Sacré-Coeur. the
Benedictines work on their backhand.

481
01:00:06.400 --> 01:00:10.400
The temperature is 24° C.
the moisture content is 70°..

482
01:00:10.400 --> 01:00:13.400
..and the atmospheric pressure
990 millibar.
